Western countries blamed President Bashar al-Assad&#8217;s armed forces for the worst poison gas attack in Syria for more than four years. WASHINGTON DC - US Defence Secretary Jim Mattis said on Wednesday that a poison gas attack in Syria was a heinous act and would be treated as such. Speaking at the Pentagon before a meeting with his counterpart from Singapore, Mattis did not elaborate on what that would mean.Western countries, including the United States, blamed Syrian President Bashar al-Assad s armed forces for the worst poison gas attack in Syria for more than four years, which choked scores of people to death in the town of Khan Sheikhoun in a rebel-held area on Tuesday.